9.Overview of the Code:
This project is a JavaScript-based single-page website where different sections are shown and hidden dynamically using the showSection() function.

Key Functionalities:
Navigation System:
JavaScript switches sections without reloading the page
Dynamic Content:
“Show Tip” button displays health advice
Progress Bar Animation:
Uses setInterval() to animate fitness progress
BMI Calculator:
Calculates BMI using user input (height & weight)
Form Validation:
Ensures required fields are filled before submission
Design:
CSS is used for layout, colors, and responsiveness
Flexbox is used for image alignment
Gradient background improves UI appearance
  
10.Conclusion
This project demonstrates how HTML, CSS, and JavaScript can be combined to create an interactive and user-friendly website. It simulates real-world web applications with features like navigation, validation, and calculations.
